{"key":"processedPost-12822406","value":{"id":12822406,"first":12821914,"last":12822510,"when":1277824140,"utime":"06/29/10 06:09 PM","cleanedPost":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><strong>jimmy8 said:</strong><br />I took your advice and put my hygrometer directly on top of the perlite, in the middle of the FC. Already it is reading 100% humidity!<br /><b>So I guess sticking the hygrometer to one of the FC walls gives inaccurate readings</b>?</blockquote><br />Exactly.&nbsp; The holes in the sides admit air from your room, which will be at a lower humidity than the air within the terrarium.&nbsp; If your hygrometer is against one of those holes, room air is passing right through the hygrometer.&nbsp; Probably the best thing is to hang the hygrometer from a wire attached to the center of the lid, so it sits near the center of the chamber.&nbsp; <br />However, if you (or anyone else reading this) built your shotgun terrarium per the tek, you can put the hygrometer away and forget it. Your humidity IS fine.<br />RR"}}